 AlgoVisualizer – JavaFX Project

AlgoVisualizer is a simple desktop application built with Java, JavaFX, and Maven that visually demonstrates how sorting algorithms work step by step.  
This project is designed for beginners in **Java + DSA** who want to showcase a practical project on GitHub.



 Features
- Visualizes **Bubble Sort** and **Insertion Sort** in action.
- Interactive UI with **JavaFX**.
- **Reset** option to shuffle and reload random data.
- Beginner-friendly code structure (easy to extend with more algorithms).



 Tech Stack
- **Java 17**
- **JavaFX 20**
- **Maven** (for build & dependency management)



 Project Structure
AlgoVisualizer/
│── pom.xml
│── src/
    └── main/
        └── java/
            └── com/example/algovisualizer/
                │── Main.java
                │── SortingVisualizer.java
                │── algorithms/
                │     ├── BubbleSort.java
                │     └── InsertionSort.java
                └── ui/
                      └── SortingPane.java
